HEADWORD: Nihil
<hw>Ni"hil</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety>
<def>Nothing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Nihil album</b></col> <ety>[L., white nothing]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>oxide of zinc.</cd> See under <er>Zinc</er>. --
<col><b>Nihil debet</b></col> <ety>[L., he owes nothing]</ety>
<fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>the general issue in certain actions of debt.</cd>
-- <col><b>Nihil dicit</b></col> <ety>[L., he says nothing]</ety>
<fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>a declinature by the defendant to plead or
answer.</cd> <rj><au>Tomlins.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nihilism</ent>⟦br⟧
